<br>
If our discussion is over your head, or if you are unable to see past your own personal biases(as Fynal and I are attempting to do), I suggest that you kept your opinions to yourself.  I'd rather not have this thread moved over to rants, that forum is crowded enough as it is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Err, Forum Arch Mage?</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/02 12:13:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=698.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages.... &lt;glare&gt;</span><hr size=1> Well, as promised, here's my response.<br>
<br>
To Fynalwiz,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I still disagree about the fast damage thing. I think it's very situational, and quite frankly, I cant remember the last time I had to burn down a mob. As you mentioned there's usually someone CCing in the group, and if it gets beyond thier capabilities I am likely to evac--not burn them down.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well, yes it's situational, that was kind of my point.  In a situation of your choosing, you can exceed the damage output of any melee.  In a lower level group, the important situation might be the Ghoul Scribe(not a ton of hp.. Quickly!  Kill that motherfucker before he charms someone!).  The key point is that once a battle starts, you'll either win or you'll lose.  If the outcome is not certian, then a wizard can choose to be the most valuable damage dealer there.  Losing is basically the worst thing that can happen to any group.  Evacuating is often sort of a get out of jail free card..  you still go to jail, you've still wasted a turn, you don't collect $200, but you don't have to wait three turns to get going again again.  In any given fight, the wizard can choose to minimize the chance of losing by outdamaging everyone.  <br>
<br>
Also, you don't have to be high level to raid.  You don't have to waste 50 levels playing a boring game so that you can get to the good stuff.  You also don't have to wait for an enchanter to do anything.<br>
<br>
Tracker tells the group, 'Hey, Thistle Underbrush on track, cons yellow.. wan't me to pull him?'<br>
<br>
A_Friend29 tells you, 'Hey Fynal, I'm looking for some people to help me kill these three necros in rathe mountians for a quest want to help?'<br>
<br>
A_Friend34 tells you, 'We got a hunting party here headed to Dalnir for some fun and loots, we could use a nuker for those nasty casters, you want to come?'<br>
<br>
A_Friend42 tells you, 'The Corrupted Earthworm is up!  Can you come help me take him out?'<br>
<br>
Someone53 tells the guild, 'Anyone not busy want to come help me kill Cazel?'<br>
<br>
A_Friend60 tells you, 'Want to come kill Dragons in West Wastes?'<br>
<br>
